article.headline: American 70, Wagner 49
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP)-- Andre Ingram scored 17 points and American shot 70 percent from the field in the second half in a 70-49 victory over Wagner on Tuesday night. The Eagles (1-2) avoided their third straight 0-3 start by hitting 14 of 20 shots after halftime, including three 3-pointers during a decisive 15-0 run. Jamal Webb and Matt Vitale scored 17 points to lead the Seahawks (0-2), who shot 32 percent and committed 16 turnovers. With the Eagles holding a 40-36 lead, Matej Cresnik started the big second half run with one of this three 3-pointers. American continued to build the advantage with four points from Patrick Okpwae and 3-pointers from reserve point guard Ryan Graham and Cresnik. Okpwae finished with 12 points and Cresnik scored 11. Webb and Vitale were the only two players for Wagner to score for the first 12:30 of the game. The Seahawks hit 7 of 20 3-pointers in the contest. Ingram keyed a keyed a 10-2 run with two 3-pointers of his own over the final 6:04 of the half to help American take a 30-21 lead.
